trying to perfect
something all by themselves,

00:23:21.366 --> 00:23:24.666 A:middle
but an entrepreneur is somebody
who really puts themselves

00:23:24.666 --> 00:23:27.556 A:middle
out there, tells as
many people as they can

00:23:27.556 --> 00:23:29.766 A:middle
about what they're passionate
about, what they're working on,

00:23:30.016 --> 00:23:33.036 A:middle
and builds a community around
them to be a part of it.

00:23:33.036 --> 00:23:35.496 A:middle
And I realized that all
along I'd been acting

00:23:35.496 --> 00:23:38.196 A:middle
like an inventor, I
was a total hermit,

00:23:38.196 --> 00:23:40.156 A:middle
and that was lonely, too.

00:23:40.786 --> 00:23:44.776 A:middle
And now I had this whole group
of people who believed in me

00:23:44.876 --> 00:23:47.526 A:middle
and believed in GoldieBlox,
who wanted to be a part of it,

00:23:47.526 --> 00:23:51.486 A:middle
and not only that could
actually help make it better.

00:23:51.486 --> 00:23:54.796 A:middle
So from that day forward
my whole view shifted.

00:23:54.796 --> 00:23:59.706 A:middle
After I left the conference,
the people there started showing

00:23:59.706 --> 00:24:01.466 A:middle
up in my apartment every day,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:59.706 --> 00:24:01.466 A:middle
up in my apartment every day,

00:24:01.746 --> 00:24:03.326 A:middle
and they started
bringing their friends,

00:24:03.746 --> 00:24:05.566 A:middle
and their friends
brought their friends.

00:24:06.116 --> 00:24:08.806 A:middle
And this group of passionate
people gave me the energy

00:24:08.806 --> 00:24:10.376 A:middle
that I needed to
get excited again,

00:24:10.506 --> 00:24:12.976 A:middle
and we started building
prototypes

00:24:12.976 --> 00:24:14.396 A:middle
and encouraging each other.

00:24:15.416 --> 00:24:18.086 A:middle
We even started a blog
where we'd write stories

00:24:18.086 --> 00:24:19.426 A:middle
about what we were
learning and the challenges

00:24:19.576 --> 00:24:22.146 A:middle
that we were facing, and we'd
share it with all our friends

00:24:22.146 --> 00:24:24.146 A:middle
and family and find
more people to help.

00:24:25.496 --> 00:24:28.226 A:middle
And with the help of
this crew of people,

00:24:28.756 --> 00:24:31.476 A:middle
we built GoldieBlox
prototypes and took them all

00:24:31.476 --> 00:24:34.206 A:middle
around the Bay area, into
people's homes and schools,

00:24:34.206 --> 00:24:37.336 A:middle
to Maker Faire to
test it on kids.

00:24:37.926 --> 00:24:40.926 A:middle
It was a process of rapid
prototyping, and the great thing

00:24:40.926 --> 00:24:44.276 A:middle
about it is since we had no
money we didn't get too married

00:24:44.276 --> 00:24:46.826 A:middle
to any one idea, we just
put it out in front of kids

00:24:46.826 --> 00:24:47.806 A:middle
and see what they thought.

00:24:48.266 --> 00:24:50.446 A:middle
We just really wanted to
know what was going to work

00:24:50.446 --> 00:24:52.096 A:middle
with the girls, what
they wanted.

00:24:52.626 --> 00:24:54.306 A:middle
And, finally, after
months and months

00:24:54.306 --> 00:24:57.156 A:middle
of testing we had a product
that I really believed in.

00:24:58.386 --> 00:25:01.416 A:middle
This was our first toy,
it's called GoldieBlox


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:58.386 --> 00:25:01.416 A:middle
This was our first toy,
it's called GoldieBlox

00:25:01.416 --> 00:25:02.646 A:middle
and the Spinning Machine.

00:25:03.206 --> 00:25:07.586 A:middle
In it we have our story, a book
about Goldie and her dog, Nacho,

00:25:07.936 --> 00:25:09.346 A:middle
who is always chasing his tail.

00:25:09.996 --> 00:25:12.336 A:middle
So Goldie decides, I'm
going to spin Nacho.

00:25:12.806 --> 00:25:16.036 A:middle
By using a wheel and an axle,
she builds a spinning machine.

00:25:16.956 --> 00:25:20.326 A:middle
But soon her other animal
friends want to spin, too.

00:25:20.736 --> 00:25:22.486 A:middle
So Goldie invents a belt drive

00:25:22.826 --> 00:25:24.956 A:middle
where she gets everybody
spinning all at once.

00:25:26.296 --> 00:25:28.836 A:middle
This product, you know,
as simple as it sounds,

00:25:29.116 --> 00:25:30.636 A:middle
really did engage
the little girls.

00:25:30.796 --> 00:25:35.066 A:middle
I had girls in tutus pounding
their fists on the table,

00:25:35.066 --> 00:25:37.716 A:middle
we have to have everybody spin!

00:25:38.356 --> 00:25:40.236 A:middle
So it works.

00:25:40.576 --> 00:25:44.256 A:middle
And it was back to all of
the research that I had done,

00:25:44.466 --> 00:25:46.346 A:middle
creating the scenarios
where everybody wins,

00:25:46.416 --> 00:25:48.416 A:middle
engaging with story,
having nurturing,

00:25:48.416 --> 00:25:49.816 A:middle
having pets and characters.

00:25:50.256 --> 00:25:54.856 A:middle
I knew it worked, but the
problem was I knew not a single

00:25:54.856 --> 00:25:57.566 A:middle
toy store was going to buy
it because they didn't think

00:25:57.566 --> 00:25:58.666 A:middle
that girls like building.

00:25:59.296 --> 00:26:02.936 A:middle
Also, I only had $2,000
left in my bank account


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:25:59.296 --> 00:26:02.936 A:middle
Also, I only had $2,000
left in my bank account

00:26:02.996 --> 00:26:06.176 A:middle
so that was not good
either, and in order

00:26:06.176 --> 00:26:10.256 A:middle
to actually produce
GoldieBlox I needed $150,000

00:26:10.566 --> 00:26:12.186 A:middle
for a first manufacturing run.

00:26:13.406 --> 00:26:16.316 A:middle
So I had to set out with
my next audacious goal,

00:26:18.156 --> 00:26:19.686 A:middle
Kickstart a movement.

00:26:20.796 --> 00:26:24.226 A:middle
I decided if the toy store
owners weren't going to buy it,

00:26:24.226 --> 00:26:27.176 A:middle
I was going to need to
crowdfund it and prove

00:26:27.176 --> 00:26:28.116 A:middle
that there was market demand.

00:26:29.446 --> 00:26:31.986 A:middle
So as everyone knows
with Kickstarter,

00:26:32.126 --> 00:26:36.706 A:middle
in order to crush it you need
an amazing video, and so I got

00:26:36.776 --> 00:26:40.236 A:middle
to work plotting out
the perfect video plan.

00:26:41.246 --> 00:26:42.726 A:middle
First, I convinced a friend

00:26:42.726 --> 00:26:45.316 A:middle
to let me use his
beautiful workshop, you know,

00:26:45.316 --> 00:26:46.636 A:middle
make it seem really cool.

00:26:47.186 --> 00:26:49.126 A:middle
Then I convinced my husband,

00:26:49.126 --> 00:26:50.966 A:middle
who owned a video
production company,

00:26:51.556 --> 00:26:54.436 A:middle
to use all of their best --

00:26:54.646 --> 00:27:00.946 A:middle
I know it's like kind of a
helpful think I know, I know,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:26:54.646 --> 00:27:00.946 A:middle
I know it's like kind of a
helpful think I know, I know,

00:27:00.946 --> 00:27:02.736 A:middle
I know -- but convince
him to film this video

00:27:02.736 --> 00:27:06.106 A:middle
with the best equipment,
lighting, camera people.

00:27:06.686 --> 00:27:08.996 A:middle
And I memorized this
perfect script,

00:27:09.406 --> 00:27:10.896 A:middle
the whole thing memorized.

00:27:11.536 --> 00:27:14.996 A:middle
Got my hair done, my makeup,
went out and bought a new dress.

00:27:15.746 --> 00:27:18.666 A:middle
I was all set, ready to
go, and brought in all

00:27:18.666 --> 00:27:20.216 A:middle
of these people to come help.

00:27:20.386 --> 00:27:24.666 A:middle
We filmed the video and
we were right on time,

00:27:24.666 --> 00:27:26.516 A:middle
we were about to
launch the campaign

00:27:26.646 --> 00:27:28.116 A:middle
in a week, everything was set.

00:27:28.636 --> 00:27:31.886 A:middle
And then the film crew sent
me the first cut of the video

00:27:32.736 --> 00:27:40.256 A:middle
and my heart sank, it was
too good, it felt staged,

00:27:40.576 --> 00:27:42.806 A:middle
it just didn't feel like
me, it wasn't genuine.

00:27:43.426 --> 00:27:46.626 A:middle
You see, when I tell people
face to face about my passion

00:27:46.626 --> 00:27:49.656 A:middle
for GoldieBlox, they get it and
they believe it and they want

00:27:49.656 --> 00:27:51.576 A:middle
to be a part of it,
but this video was

00:27:51.576 --> 00:27:55.066 A:middle
so overdone it just wasn't
reading, it didn't feel natural.

00:27:55.716 --> 00:27:59.146 A:middle
And so even though we only had
a couple days left before the

00:27:59.146 --> 00:28:01.646 A:middle
Kickstarter was going to
go live, and even though


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:27:59.146 --> 00:28:01.646 A:middle
Kickstarter was going to
go live, and even though

00:28:01.646 --> 00:28:04.096 A:middle
so many people had
helped me make this video

00:28:04.096 --> 00:28:05.986 A:middle
and I felt really bad, I had

00:28:05.986 --> 00:28:09.416 A:middle
to scrap the whole thing,
I had to reshoot it.

00:28:10.216 --> 00:28:13.106 A:middle
Literally, we had two days left,
on the floor of my apartment.

00:28:14.166 --> 00:28:17.536 A:middle
And in order to get
comfortable enough to be myself

00:28:17.676 --> 00:28:20.456 A:middle
when a video camera was
staring at me six inches away

00:28:20.506 --> 00:28:23.216 A:middle
from my face I had to
drink three-quarters

00:28:23.216 --> 00:28:23.976 A:middle
of a bottle of wine.

00:28:24.516 --> 00:28:29.896 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:28:30.396 --> 00:28:33.306 A:middle
Actually, I just did that
backstage -- no, just kidding.

00:28:34.046 --> 00:28:38.956 A:middle
But finally after hundreds of
takes, no script, I just spoke

00:28:38.956 --> 00:28:41.296 A:middle
from the heart, and that
was actually the footage

00:28:41.296 --> 00:28:44.556 A:middle
that we used once we cut out
all of the slurring parts.

00:28:48.126 --> 00:28:50.586 A:middle
Next order of business,
we had the video

00:28:50.646 --> 00:28:52.556 A:middle
and now we needed the support.

00:28:53.166 --> 00:28:55.346 A:middle
In true create your
own luck form,

00:28:55.786 --> 00:28:59.486 A:middle
we created this serial
killer-style list of all

00:28:59.486 --> 00:29:02.336 A:middle
of the people that we knew
we had to let them know


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:59.486 --> 00:29:02.336 A:middle
of the people that we knew
we had to let them know

00:29:02.336 --> 00:29:04.986 A:middle
about GoldieBlox in hopes
that they would share it --

00:29:05.276 --> 00:29:08.286 A:middle
celebrities, journalists,
people with big audiences,

00:29:08.286 --> 00:29:12.296 A:middle
everyone we could who we thought
could help get the word out.

00:29:12.996 --> 00:29:15.666 A:middle
And then we started mapping
them, who are these people,

00:29:15.666 --> 00:29:16.596 A:middle
how can we get to them?

00:29:16.596 --> 00:29:18.236 A:middle
Does someone know
someone who knows someone

00:29:18.236 --> 00:29:21.086 A:middle
who can get to Hillary Clinton?

00:29:21.386 --> 00:29:24.536 A:middle
And we maniacally
schemed and plotted.

00:29:25.066 --> 00:29:27.996 A:middle
One of the people on this
list was Tim Schafer,

00:29:28.796 --> 00:29:30.956 A:middle
and I'll just tell the story
of how I got a hold of him.

00:29:31.406 --> 00:29:33.926 A:middle
He was one of many
examples of the people

00:29:33.926 --> 00:29:35.336 A:middle
who we relentlessly stalked.

00:29:36.156 --> 00:29:38.986 A:middle
So after stalking Tim I found --

00:29:39.216 --> 00:29:40.846 A:middle
and Tim, for those of
you who don't know,

00:29:40.846 --> 00:29:43.936 A:middle
legendary videogame designer
and Kickstarter celebrity.

00:29:44.556 --> 00:29:49.986 A:middle
After stalking him, I found
out that we used the same bank,

00:29:50.076 --> 00:29:55.426 A:middle
so I emailed my banker and
sat down with him for a cup

00:29:55.426 --> 00:29:57.856 A:middle
of coffee and kind of just
sort of brought it up,

00:29:57.856 --> 00:29:59.176 A:middle
and he was like, oh,
you should meet Tim.

00:29:59.436 --> 00:30:01.576 A:middle
I'm like, yes, yes,
I'd love to meet Tim.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:29:59.436 --> 00:30:01.576 A:middle
I'm like, yes, yes,
I'd love to meet Tim.

00:30:02.386 --> 00:30:03.766 A:middle
And before I knew it,

00:30:03.916 --> 00:30:05.996 A:middle
I'm hanging out at the
office of Double Fine.

00:30:06.676 --> 00:30:10.496 A:middle
And it turns out Tim had a
daughter, and he was interested

00:30:10.496 --> 00:30:11.426 A:middle
in what we were doing.

00:30:11.996 --> 00:30:15.596 A:middle
So I made the ask, I said,
Tim, would you be willing

00:30:15.596 --> 00:30:18.046 A:middle
to let me film you playing
GoldieBlox with your daughter?

00:30:18.636 --> 00:30:19.436 A:middle
And he said, sure.

00:30:20.346 --> 00:30:23.246 A:middle
So we got them together, filmed
them playing for the first time,

00:30:23.246 --> 00:30:26.096 A:middle
and it was really magical
because she loved it and it was

00:30:26.136 --> 00:30:27.566 A:middle
so cute seeing them
play it together.

00:30:27.596 --> 00:30:29.746 A:middle
It was really a genuine
moment, and we actually put it

00:30:29.746 --> 00:30:30.836 A:middle
in our video as a cameo.

00:30:32.696 --> 00:30:36.386 A:middle
And the day that the Kickstarter
went live, it exploded.

00:30:36.786 --> 00:30:40.766 A:middle
First, Tim Schafer tweeted it to
his 90,000 Kickstarter backers.

00:30:41.816 --> 00:30:45.466 A:middle
Then, as it turned out,
reporters from TechCrunch

00:30:45.466 --> 00:30:48.676 A:middle
and The Atlantic had been
reading my blog the whole time,

00:30:48.976 --> 00:30:51.866 A:middle
and so when our campaign
went live they wrote articles

00:30:51.866 --> 00:30:53.126 A:middle
about it.

00:30:53.286 --> 00:30:57.786 A:middle
Our goal of raising $150,000,
we reached it in only four days.

00:30:58.326 --> 00:31:00.076 A:middle
A friend of mine who
works at Facebook sent it


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:30:58.326 --> 00:31:00.076 A:middle
A friend of mine who
works at Facebook sent it

00:31:00.076 --> 00:31:02.556 A:middle
to Sheryl Sandberg, and
she became a backer.

00:31:03.126 --> 00:31:06.796 A:middle
My aunt knew someone who knew
someone, who knew Craig Newmark

00:31:06.796 --> 00:31:10.176 A:middle
of Craigslist, he backed
it and he tweeted it.

00:31:10.606 --> 00:31:15.266 A:middle
So it just totally exploded,
and the craziest thing is

00:31:15.266 --> 00:31:17.416 A:middle
that Upworthy posted the video,

00:31:17.416 --> 00:31:21.076 A:middle
and it went so viral
online we ended

00:31:21.076 --> 00:31:23.196 A:middle
up selling almost
a million dollars

00:31:23.336 --> 00:31:25.106 A:middle
of GoldieBlox in preorders.

00:31:26.006 --> 00:31:27.976 A:middle
It was overwhelming,
to say the least.

00:31:28.516 --> 00:31:34.986 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:31:35.486 --> 00:31:37.016 A:middle
And I finally had
money in the bank.

00:31:37.016 --> 00:31:41.126 A:middle
I made my first hire, Lindsey,
she left her job, took the leap,

00:31:41.126 --> 00:31:45.306 A:middle
came onboard, and the next day
we got an email from Toys R Us,

00:31:46.416 --> 00:31:48.466 A:middle
which led us to our
next audacious goal:

00:31:48.866 --> 00:31:51.236 A:middle
disrupt the pink aisle.

00:31:52.416 --> 00:31:54.636 A:middle
So Toys R Us calls
and they said,

00:31:54.636 --> 00:31:55.676 A:middle
we'd like to meet with you.

00:31:55.926 --> 00:31:59.976 A:middle
So Lindsey and I get on a plane
and we fly to Wayne, New Jersey,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:32:00.546 --> 00:32:03.646 A:middle
and we get into the meeting

00:32:03.646 --> 00:32:07.246 A:middle
with these Toys R Us
executives, these men in suits.

00:32:07.576 --> 00:32:10.026 A:middle
And in part of the Kickstarter
video, I was skulking

00:32:10.026 --> 00:32:12.776 A:middle
through the pink aisle holding
up a picture of GoldieBlox next

00:32:12.776 --> 00:32:16.006 A:middle
to Barbie, it was
obviously like at Toys R Us.

00:32:16.006 --> 00:32:19.346 A:middle
And the Toys R Us guys were
like, so what's up with

00:32:19.756 --> 00:32:21.096 A:middle
that part in your video

00:32:21.256 --> 00:32:23.776 A:middle
where you're making
us look really bad?

00:32:24.446 --> 00:32:25.786 A:middle
I'm like, sorry.

00:32:26.416 --> 00:32:28.946 A:middle
And it turned out that the
head construction toy buyer

00:32:28.946 --> 00:32:32.106 A:middle
at Toys R Us had two daughters,
and he said, you know,

00:32:32.186 --> 00:32:33.456 A:middle
GoldieBlox is the
kind of product

00:32:33.456 --> 00:32:34.736 A:middle
that I want for my girls.

00:32:35.346 --> 00:32:38.456 A:middle
And sure enough, six months
later we're on the shelves

00:32:38.456 --> 00:32:40.276 A:middle
of Toys R Us nationwide.

00:32:41.266 --> 00:32:44.486 A:middle
I remember going in there
and looking at our products

00:32:44.486 --> 00:32:47.736 A:middle
on the shelf for the first
time, and I had tears in my eyes

00:32:47.846 --> 00:32:50.436 A:middle
because we had set this
audacious goal, yes,

00:32:50.566 --> 00:32:53.766 A:middle
we'll be in Toys R Us, and
never thought it would happen

00:32:53.766 --> 00:32:56.566 A:middle
so quickly, that all of
that hard work and passion

00:32:56.566 --> 00:32:59.796 A:middle
and belief could
actually happen.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

