first doll on the moon is
actually one of our goals.

00:47:01.956 --> 00:47:04.906 A:middle
And how can we be so audacious?

00:47:04.906 --> 00:47:08.526 A:middle
Well, it's because at the end of
the day, the mission is greater

00:47:08.526 --> 00:47:11.026 A:middle
than our company, and I
never feel embarrassed going

00:47:11.066 --> 00:47:13.966 A:middle
and asking somebody for help
or asking somebody to be a part

00:47:13.966 --> 00:47:15.796 A:middle
of it because it's
bigger than all of us.

00:47:16.336 --> 00:47:20.066 A:middle
We really believe in it,
and I'm reminded every day

00:47:20.066 --> 00:47:24.456 A:middle
that it's working because
every day we see evidence

00:47:24.856 --> 00:47:26.716 A:middle
of girls getting
inspired by GoldieBlox.

00:47:27.566 --> 00:47:31.296 A:middle
Recently I got a letter from
a mom, she was telling me

00:47:31.296 --> 00:47:35.066 A:middle
that her daughter was not
excited to go to science camp,

00:47:35.676 --> 00:47:37.926 A:middle
that every morning her
daughter would whine and whine

00:47:37.926 --> 00:47:39.636 A:middle
and she'd have to
drag her to camp.

00:47:39.636 --> 00:47:40.746 A:middle
Her daughter didn't want to go

00:47:40.746 --> 00:47:42.656 A:middle
because the camp
was almost all boys.

00:47:43.746 --> 00:47:46.816 A:middle
And then her mom bought her
GoldieBlox and they played it

00:47:46.816 --> 00:47:48.566 A:middle
over the weekend
together, they had a blast.

00:47:49.436 --> 00:47:51.626 A:middle
On Monday they were
getting ready to go to camp,

00:47:51.626 --> 00:47:54.896 A:middle
and her daughter wasn't
having her usual crying fit.

00:47:55.946 --> 00:47:59.226 A:middle
And her Mom asked her what's
going on with you, you know,

00:47:59.976 --> 00:48:03.066 A:middle
what's going on, and why aren't
you nervous about camp anymore?


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:47:59.976 --> 00:48:03.066 A:middle
what's going on, and why aren't
you nervous about camp anymore?

00:48:03.446 --> 00:48:06.406 A:middle
And her daughter said, oh, Mom,
I'm not nervous about camp,

00:48:06.406 --> 00:48:09.486 A:middle
I've got GoldieBlox,
I'm all set.

00:48:09.816 --> 00:48:12.346 A:middle
And I know it sounds like
I'm making this story up,

00:48:12.346 --> 00:48:14.656 A:middle
but I'm actually not,
like, this really happened.

00:48:15.056 --> 00:48:19.516 A:middle
And it's amazing because with
GoldieBlox we're starting

00:48:19.516 --> 00:48:21.486 A:middle
to give these girls
a role model,

00:48:21.666 --> 00:48:25.106 A:middle
somebody who they can
see themselves being.

00:48:25.426 --> 00:48:27.956 A:middle
And we're not just teaching
them some engineering lessons,

00:48:28.016 --> 00:48:30.156 A:middle
but we're actually
giving them confidence.

00:48:30.156 --> 00:48:32.846 A:middle
And that's what we,
all of us here,

00:48:32.846 --> 00:48:35.196 A:middle
have the opportunity to do.

00:48:35.706 --> 00:48:39.166 A:middle
We can help kids shape the
way that they see the world,

00:48:39.876 --> 00:48:41.726 A:middle
whether it's the
products that we build

00:48:41.886 --> 00:48:44.236 A:middle
or just the things
that we say to kids.

00:48:44.236 --> 00:48:47.926 A:middle
I mean think about it, every
time you see a little girl

00:48:47.926 --> 00:48:49.606 A:middle
and you tell her that
she looks beautiful,

00:48:50.146 --> 00:48:51.596 A:middle
imagine what a difference
it would make

00:48:51.596 --> 00:48:54.886 A:middle
if you said she looks capable?


