making a game or a movie

00:49:05.136 --> 00:49:09.646 A:middle
and you're choosing a hero and
you automatically make it a boy,

00:49:10.736 --> 00:49:12.836 A:middle
what if you made it
a girl, you know?

00:49:13.656 --> 00:49:15.656 A:middle
Sometimes we propagate
gender stereotypes

00:49:15.656 --> 00:49:18.756 A:middle
and we don't even realize
it, but the cool thing is

00:49:19.216 --> 00:49:20.846 A:middle
that we have the
opportunity to change that.

00:49:21.676 --> 00:49:24.226 A:middle
There's no pink or blue
aisle in the App Store,

00:49:24.396 --> 00:49:28.086 A:middle
and we get to put stuff
out there that, you know,

00:49:28.086 --> 00:49:30.746 A:middle
kids are so impressionable,
we can put stuff

00:49:30.746 --> 00:49:32.576 A:middle
out there that's going to
make them see the world

00:49:32.576 --> 00:49:33.276 A:middle
in a whole new way.

00:49:33.446 --> 00:49:36.946 A:middle
And if we do that, and if you
all join me on this mission,

00:49:37.916 --> 00:49:40.676 A:middle
we can achieve my last and
final audacious goal --

00:49:41.536 --> 00:49:44.596 A:middle
that sometime in our
own lifetime 50 percent

00:49:44.806 --> 00:49:46.586 A:middle
of WWDC is women.

00:49:47.506 --> 00:49:47.976 A:middle
Thank you.

